    h6 Deep Learning for Computer Vision
    p The lectures for this class started off discussing basic neural networks, and then quickly advanced to talking about CNNs before getting to state of the art techniques. For this class I read 5-10 papers on recent techniques used. The lectures also touched on RNNs, LSTMs, auto-encoders, and neural turing machines. There were 3 assignments for the class:
      ol
        li Implementing a neural network from scratch, and deriving the equation for back propagation
        li Simple CNN classifier, creating adversarial example using Keras
        li Reinforcement learning with MDP, RNN with handpicked weights
