    h6 Web Security
    p In this class I learned all about the basics of web security including XSS, CSRF, click jacking, CSP, SOP, and SQL injection. This class had 6 well crafted labs in which I did things such as set up a load balancer, create an HTTP client, and pentest a website the professor made. The project for the class is where I learned the most. I made a website like twitter which was distributed across 4 different web services and involved using MySQL for storing user credentials and ElasticSearch for the tweets. In addition to building the system I had to make sure it was secure to prevent things like CSRF, XSS, password cracking, and SQL injection. 
