    h6 Real Time and Embedded Systems
    p The first half of the semester focused on writing bare metal applications. In teams of 2 we made a primitive signal analyzer and a basic servo motor controller. The second half of the semester involved writing applications using FreeRTOS so that we could make use of threads. We built a bank simulation, and then a threaded servo controller. To finish off the semester we built a game where the computer controls one servo motor and the player controls the other by tilting the STM32 board. The player tries to move their servo to match the computer's servo in a set amount of time. 
    p In this class I learned about signals, basic circuits, and how to read the STM32 manual to interact with all of the peripherals that the board offers. I learned how to use the timers, signal receiver, signal generator, UART, and gyroscope.
